&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Clinical Fellow in Urology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Senior Clinical Fellow in Urology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts are intended for those who have completed basic surgical training or equivalent experience with attainment of MRCS. These posts are an ideal opportunity for the successful candidate to gain more experience in urology and improve their competitiveness at National Selection for higher training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department of Urology at Whittington Health NHS Trust is a friendly and dynamic one. There will be regular theatre lists with exposure to core and general urology, laparoscopic upper tract surgery as well as PCNL. The successful applicant will also have opportunity to develop surgical skills. The successful applicant will be supported to develop audit projects, give presentations and take part in educational activities in order to enhance their CV.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMr Barry MarajJob titleConsultantEmail addressbarry.maraj@nhs.netAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; Should you wish to get further details about this post, please do not hesitate to contact&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mr Barry Maraj: barry.maraj@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
